    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 is a peerless example of the FD3S generation, featuring a factory-original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The longitudinal front-midship layout provides a perfect 50:50 weight distribution, complemented by a fully serviced double-wishbone suspension and a tight Torsen limited-slip differential. The powertrain maintains exceptional compression across all rotors, and the five-speed manual transmission delivers precise, short-throw engagement. Every vacuum line and cooling component has been preserved to ensure thermal efficiency, making this an unmodified, investment-grade specimen. The exterior and interior are in concours-level condition, free from the typical wear associated with high-performance vehicles of this era.",
      "price": 48500.0,
